          "date": "2012-02-26 09:20:10.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-1126 ldlm: ensure correct deref if lock mode changes",
        "message": "LU-1126 ldlm: ensure correct deref if lock mode changes\n\nIf a lock is granted in different mode other than it is\noriginally requested, it is possible to trigger LBUG because\nof incorrect lock dereference.\n\ne.g., LBUG code path:\nldlm_lock_create()->ldlm_lock_addref(PW)\nserver returns PR lock\nldlm_cli_enqueue_fini() sets lock->l_req_mode to PR\nldlm_grant_lock() sets lock->l_grant_mode to l_req_mode(PR)\nldlm_process_flock_lock() finds the lock and tries to destroy it\nwith ldlm_flock_destroy(lock->l_grant_mode)\n\nSigned-off-by: Peng Tao <tao.peng@emc.com>\nChange-Id: I1277ea80b9e754f926859532d88ddce2a292ec5c\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b1_8"
    }
  },
